social_posts.post_text: Congrats to @canfar1987 on raising over $1.3 million at this year’s Bloor Street Entertains 💥🎉 Extra proud to call one of the co-chairs, @candice_t_sinclair, a best friend. You knocked it out of the park! If you’re not familiar, CANFAR does vital work to help end the HIV epidemic 👏🏼👏🏼 I wore all Canadian 🇨🇦 for the occasion #wearcanadaproud

Congrats to all the inductees and honourees at last night’s Canadas’s Walk of Fame @cwofame gala, including @thetragicallyhip @deborahcox @arkellsmusic @directorx + more inspiring and impactful Canadians 🇨🇦 👏🏼 Of course I wore 🍁 too #wearcanadaproud

Amazing to be back in-person with over 200 audience members and 1,000 watching virtually at yesterday’s 46th @cdnclubto annual political & economic outlook lunch 🙌🏼🙏🏼 It was my pleasure as moderator to lead a thought-provoking discussion (and, at times, debate!) with some of the country’s top minds on the most pressing issues for Canada in 2023 🇨🇦 🔮 Do you have any predictions for the year ahead? #cdnpoli
I joined @nationalpost Ottawa Bureau Chief John Ivison’s weekly show to take stock of the state of Canadian federal politics as life returns to Parliament Hill. Link to full video in bio!

Now online! Me, @benspurr, @jennifer_keesmaat + @marcusbgee join @spaikin on @theagendatvo to discuss John Tory's (supposed?) resignation, his legacy, and what happens next for Toronto. LINK IN BIO 🎞️

Scenes from my fireside chat with Ontario Labour & Immigration Minister @montemcnaughton for @empire_club this week. We had a great conversation about how his Working for Workers acts address key issues that’ve been ignored for too long, including safe washrooms on construction sites, opening new paths to the skilled trades, layoff protections for remote workers, getting more newcomers working in their trained fields and more. Ontario’s economic future starts with workers ✅

ICYMI— catch up on my latest @nationalpost columns via the link in my bio! 📰 Analysis of why the housing boom is back, how Canada is failing young women & families, and NDP leader Jagmeet Singh’s economic hollowness. #cdnpoli

ICYMI- my latest @nationalpost column on how Canada is about to lose a promising tidal power venture because the feds either can’t or won’t get their act together. 

Canada, despite all our natural resources, is earning a well-deserved reputation as a place where next-generation energy projects go to die. Read via link in bio!

A few months ago I went on @theagendatvo to talk about how Alberta is attracting record numbers of young professionals & families from Ontario because of wage stagnation and unaffordable housing. This brain drain is terrible for the province and also undermines our communities & social ties. As house prices begin to rise again, these issues need to be take seriously by politicians of all levels and addressed with the urgency they require. This is a crisis. #cdnpoli #onpoli
ICYMI you can read my front-page @nationalpost column on this week’s testimony from former Pierre Elliott Trudeau Foundation CEO Morris Rosenberg via link in my bio.

Beautiful day for celebrating The King’s Coronation at Queen’s Park — rides, entertainers & free food + beverages from Ontario farmers and producers. Amazing to see so many families out enjoying the festivities!

Always love discovering a new local small business— picked up the nicest bouquet from @flowersmart for Mother’s Day… and now want to recreate their book wall at home, too! 📖📖📖 #shoplocal #shoprichmondhill #myrichmondhill #supportsmallbusiness

So impressed by the talent of graduating @artsmackenzie students at their annual “Finale” show — the future of Canadian art was here, and I can’t wait to see what these emerging artists do next! 👏🏼👏🏼 Great getting to chat with some of them about their inspiration, process, and post-secondary plans at the historic Boynton House turned gallery space. #myrichmondhill #supportlocalartists #richmondhill

Wouldn’t it be great to see a Housing Minister who has an actual stake in solving the crisis rather than one benefiting financially from it? Last week, I talked about the news Liberal Housing Minister Ahmed Hussen just bought ANOTHER rental property with @nationalpost’s John Ivison & @adamzivo. His second in two years. In any other area, this would be an obvious conflict of interest. #cdnpoli #cdnpolitics

“David Johnston could’ve easily retired in peace, but instead Trudeau recruited him back to public life to serve as what very much looks like his puppet.” 

Read my latest column on how a parliamentary crisis is brewing, thanks to the former governor general. Link in my stories or bio. #cdnpoli #canadianpolitics

A few glimpses into an amazing sold-out night at @gardinermuseum SMASH! Thank you to everyone who came out, my co-chair David Simmonds, our generous sponsors, and all the committee members for making it one to remember and a huge fundraising success for the museum— we boosted ticket revenue by over 55% from last year 🙌🏼🎉 Amazing to see so many young people out in support of the arts! 👏🏼👏🏼 Photos by @ryanemberley + @kennedypollard_
Amazing turnout & energy all afternoon at the @yorkprideca parade and festival! Couldn’t ask for a more gorgeous day to celebrate #YorkRegion Pride. This world needs more love, kindness, and freedom!

Housing affordability is a foundational issue that connects to nearly every other problem in Canadian society. 

Thanks @moreneighbourstoronto for having me out to talk housing at your @habitatgta fundraiser this week! #cdnpoli #onpoli #canadianpolitics #housingcrisis #housing

Could a “doom loop” be coming to a Canadian city near you? Many signs point to yes. Use the link in my bio to read my @nationalpost column on why chasing away the middle class is a recipe for disaster in places like Toronto and Vancouver, which should be learning some tough lessons from the state of San Francisco. 

Worse, in Canada, doom loops are less likely to stay contained to one or two cities. There’s much more potential for broad social and economic consequences if we don’t save the middle class.
Actual footage of federal Liberals discussing the housing crisis #cdnpoli #cdnpolitics #housingcrisis #affordablehousing
Increasing housing supply is key, BUT we can’t ignore the demand side of the affordability crisis. Here’s why. #cdnpoli #housingcrisis #affordablehousing

Fantastic time leading a @collisionconfhq debate between Mick Mulvaney, former acting White House Chief of Staff, and Brian Tyler Cohen, creator and podcast host, on the state of politics in 2023. We talked about topics ranging from growing partisanship to immigration and generational change. #collisionconf
Here’s what conservative candidates should have done to beat Olivia Chow. Big missed opportunity! ICYMI from @theagendatvo earlier this week 📺 #topoli #cdnpoli
🇨🇦 Happy Canada Day! 🇨🇦 So grateful and proud to call this beautiful country home! There's truly nowhere like the True North 🍁

My column on today’s @nationalpost front page or via link in my bio: Asylum seekers are being dumped on the pavement indefinitely in Toronto. 

No food, drink, or shelter. 

Families and children. 

All because the federal gov’t won’t pay the bills they’re legally responsible for.

When two @nationalpost columnists and economic enthusiasts meet for lunch, it turns into an afternoon. Great conversations today about narrowing the wealth gap, housing, healthy democracy, and more with the one and only Frank Stronach!

It’s been an unusually busy summer in politics & news, so in case you’ve missed them, catch up on my latest @nationalpost columns via the link in my bio! 

I cover issues spanning housing affordability, nonsensical plastic bans, transit failures, the rise in random violent crime + more! #cdnpoli #canadianpolitics

Canadians continue to get much less for their grocery dollar as food banks across the country see record demand, including from workers with full-time jobs! 

Worse, food banks are starting to report donation shortages because donors can barely afford to feed themselves.
A bit delayed posting, but had the best time taking my dad — a huge tennis fan — to the National Bank Open a couple weeks ago. We were lucky enough to see world no.1 @carlitosalcarazz play!
I’m leading a fireside chat with Alberta Investmemt Management Corporation CEO Evan Siddall this Tuesday for @cdnclubto — go to canadianclub.org to buy tickets or register to watch virtually!

Fantastic time leading a conversation with Alberta Investment Management Corporation CEO and former CMHC head Evan Siddall for @cdnclubto yesterday! We talked investment strategies, global markets, housing affordability and more in front of a packed house at @fairmontroyalyork. 

And, as almost always, I proudly wore Canadian for the occasion 🇨🇦: @smythebrand @sophiegraceshop. #wearcanadaproud  #shoplocal

Massive congrats to my good friend @barryavrich22 on yet another incredibly successful and entertaining @stratfest gala last night! The Canadian arts community is lucky to have you. 

📸 @ryanemberley 
Wearing 🇨🇦 @gretaconstantine 
#wearcanadaproud

Great time chatting with former Prime Minister Stephen Harper to cap off the Harper Economic Forum hosted by @canadastrongfree in Toronto last night! 

As nearly always, wearing Canadian and supporting local 🇨🇦: @smythebrand #wearcanadaproud
Join me in conversation with former Minister of Foreign Affairs John Baird next Thursday in support of @ujafederation’s Israel Emergency Fund! Link to register in my bio! @canadastrongfree
Great conversation tonight with John @Baird and Jason Kenney about how we can support Israel and combat anti-Semitism within our own borders for @canadastrongfree in support of @ujafederation! 🇨🇦 🇮🇱

On the front page of today’s @NationalPost, or via link in bio. The Israeli Consulate screened uncensored footage of the Oct 7 massacre for select media.

Over the span of 43 minutes, I watched 138 humans be murdered or witnessed their corpses.

But the worst part wasn’t the gore. It was the glee of Hamas terrorists.

I don’t know if the full footage will ever be made public, but if it ever is, every single Canadian should watch it.

Kicked off the holiday season last night supporting @shoeboxproject, an amazing charity that supports women impacted by homelessness by delivering personally crafted shoebox gifts filled with everyday essentials, little luxuries, and handwritten notes. 

If you can, make a shoebox over the next few weeks. A woman will greatly appreciate it! 

📷 @georgepimentel1

Thrilled to be a panelist at the 47th Annual @cdnclubto Economic & Political Outlook! Called “Canada’s best political economic forecast lunch,” I’ll be discussing what to expect in 2024 with esteemed co-panelists Amanda Lang, Dennis Mitchell, and Jean-Francois Perrault. Tickets avail @ canadianclub.org 🎟️

Honoured to emcee last night’s Israel’s Angels fundraiser, featuring former Prime Minister Stephen Harper, in memory of the souls lost on the Oct. 7 attacks in Israel and in support of the The Sderot Resilience Center. Over $1 million raised in one night to help heal the trauma of survivors and families! 🇮🇱 🇨🇦 

📷 @georgepimentel1

My column on tomorrow’s @nationalpost front page: The new #NOVA documentary leaves no doubt young innocents were slaughtered for zero reason but antisemitic hate, and that such an atrocity must never be allowed to happen again. 

You should watch and share it. Link to column in bio.
Officially in full Christmas mode—wishing everyone a festive season full of joy and not-so-silent nights laughing with loved ones!

2023 had no shortage of important issues to cover and injustices to bring attention to. Looking back at some of my @nationalpost cover stories from the last year, on topics from the Oct. 7 terrorist attacks on Israel to refugees abandoned on Canadian streets, government transparency & corruption, the Liberals’ internet censorship, economic opportunity for young Canadians, and much more.

2024, here we come! Big things ahead and the best teammate to do them with. 

Happy New Year, everyone! 🎉🥂

Let’s resolve to make real change when it comes to housing affordability in 2024. More building. ✅ Fewer excuses. ❌ Here’s what I think should be in, and what should stay in 2023. 

#cdnpolitics #housingcrisis #housingaffordability #affordablehousing

📣 Some personal news 📣 This was my last @NationalPost column as I take a leave to embark on new adventures. 

Stay tuned for an announcement coming soon!

Had a great time participating in @cdnclubto’s annual Political & Economic Outlook panel for 2024 alongside some of the country’s brightest minds. We discussed housing affordability, inflation, the rise of authoritarianism abroad and much more. Thank you for having me!
